The usually reclusive Ono agreed to the interview to counter Goldman's The Lives of John Lennon, which presents the ex-Beatle as a violent, drug-addicted drunk who wanted to dump his wife. A biography that portrays John Lennon as a drug-addled, anorexic bisexual who raged his way from Liverpool to New York City is totally fiction, Yoko Ono said in a national radio broadcast.  It's a very dramatically described something, but it's not about John, Ono said Wednesday night in her first broadcast comments on the book by Albert Goldman. It's not John and me, Ono continued. 